description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge? The University Medical Group in Reading has an exciting opportunity to extend the pharmacist role within primary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a large GP Practice serving 32,000 patients, we are seeking an enthusiastic and forward thinking pharmacist to join our current team which has been awarded &quot;Outstanding&quot; twice by CQC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an additional pharmacist to join our existing team of 4 pharmacists todevelop and manage all aspects of medicines within the practice and will be responsible for managing repeat prescriptions and other duties to fulfil the role of a practice based pharmacist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role forms part of the workforce development plan for the University Primary Care Network (PCN) which is a single practice PCN formed by the University Medical Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with highly skilled multi-disciplinary teams you will have a patient facing role within the surgery. This is an evolving role with huge scope for development, mentoring will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the NHS England clinical Pharmacist in General Practice 2 Programme the successful candidate will be enrolled onto the &#39;CPPE Clinical Pharmacist in General Practice Education Programm. This programme is part of the Berkshire West wide bid, and as such the successful candidates will be part of a supportive network of pharmacists across the region as well as a fully-fledged team already in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential for the role: Registration as a pharmacist with General Pharmaceutical Council&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Independent prescribing qualification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3+ years post - qualification experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
